<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="202" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1841,2012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1841,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Fastigial horns of variable height, from low in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[797,943,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittarius">
<emphasis box="[797,943,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">T. sagittarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to extremely high in 
<taxonomicName authority="Patano &amp; Mohagan &amp; Tumbrinck &amp; Amoroso &amp; Skejo, 2021" authorityName="Patano &amp; Mohagan &amp; Tumbrinck &amp; Amoroso &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2021" box="[1179,1279,1841,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derijei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1179,1279,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">T. derijei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1285,1348,1841,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1285,1341,1841,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1371,1395]" captionTargetBox="[170,1419,186,1347]" captionTargetId="figure-31@9.[165,1422,181,1347]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Morphological details of Tegotettix derijei sp. n. (holotype, female).A) head in frontal view, B) head in dorsal view, C) head in ventral view, D) head and prozona in lateral view, E)—fore femur, F)—mid femur, G) antenna, H) abdomen tip in lateral view, I) abdomen tip in ventral view, J) hind femur, K) hind tibia and tarsus. Photographed by Romeo R. Patano Jr." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4550220/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
). Lateral ocelli placed between the compound eyes. In frontal view, frontal costa extremely short before bifurcation, almost indistinct. Facial carinae after the bifurcation divergent and straight. Shoulders (humeral part of the pronotum) elegant. Prozona extremely short. Pronotum with projections only on median carina. Femora undulated or straight. Chitinous surfaces generally smooth. This groups of species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[1183,1251,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1183,1251,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">Xistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550204" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4550204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4550204/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" startId="4.[151,250,1364,1388]" targetBox="[180,1400,191,1340]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1364,1460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1364,1388]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
The last record of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1913" authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[469,818,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[469,658,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Tegotettix armatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock, J. L." box="[664,818,1364,1389]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" pagination="39 - 54" refId="ref6596" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1913) Studies of Tetriginae (Acrydinae) from Sarawak Museum, Borneo. The Sarawak Museum Journal, 1 (3), 39 - 54." type="journal article" year="1913">Hancock, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is this female from Poring caught in 1996 (see text for more details). The specimen is identified by comparison with 
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther, K." box="[710,865,1400,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" pagination="165 - 195" refId="ref6526" refString="Gunther, K. (1937) Orthoptera celebica sarasiniana, Fam. Acrididae, Subfam. Acrydiinae. Treubia, 16, 165 - 195." type="journal article" year="1937">Günther (1937)</bibRefCitation>
drawing of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[985,1092,1401,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[985,1092,1401,1424]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">T. armatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A—lateral view, B—dorsal view, C—frontal view. Photo Josef Tumbrinck.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1506,1641]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,557,1506,1533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Composition and distribution</emphasis>
. This species group includes 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stal, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[897,1299,1506,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corniculatus">
<emphasis box="[897,1155,1507,1533]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Tegotettix corniculatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[1173,1290,1506,1533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" pagination="33 - 58" refId="ref7278" refString="Stal, C. (1877) Orthoptera nova ex Insulis Philippinis descripsit. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlinger, 34 (10), 33 - 58." type="journal article" year="1877">Stål, 1877</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(the 
<collectingCountry name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Philippines</collectingCountry>
: unknown locality), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gunther, 1935) (Borneo)" authorityName="Borneo" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[440,873,1542,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristiferus">
<emphasis box="[440,580,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">T. cristiferus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther, K." box="[593,755,1542,1569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" pagination="257 - 263" refId="ref6482" refString="Gunther, K. (1935) Acrydiinen (Orth. Acrididae) aus dem mittleren Ostrorneo gesammelt von H. C. Siebers 1925. Arbeiten uber Morphologische und Taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem, 2 (4), 257 - 263." type="journal article" year="1935">Günther, 1935</bibRefCitation>
) (Borneo)
</taxonomicName>
, here described 
<taxonomicName authority="Patano &amp; Mohagan &amp; Tumbrinck &amp; Amoroso &amp; Skejo, 2021" authorityName="Patano &amp; Mohagan &amp; Tumbrinck &amp; Amoroso &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2021" box="[1049,1238,1543,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derijei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1049,1238,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Tegotettix derijei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1243,1305,1543,1569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1243,1298,1543,1569]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(the 
<collectingCountry name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Philippines</collectingCountry>
: Mindanao), and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bolivar, 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[409,738,1579,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittarius">
<emphasis box="[409,557,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">T. sagittarius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bolivar, I." box="[571,730,1579,1605]" pageId="4" pageNumber="202" pagination="175 - 313" refId="ref6398" refString="Bolivar, I. (1887) Essai sur les Acridiens de la tribu des Tettigidae. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 31, 175 - 313." type="journal article" year="1887">Bolívar, 1887</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. More new species await description within this species group (
<figureCitation box="[159,266,1615,1641]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1654,1678]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,560,1630]" captionTargetId="figure-187@6.[159,1429,560,1630]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. An undescribed Tegotettix species from the Philippines (A, B, D) with very high fastigial horns, resembling T. sagittarius and T. corniculatus. Photographed in Balinsasayao Twin Lakes Natural Park (Negros Oriental) (C) on May 17th 2017 by Veronica Prudente and reproduced with her permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550210" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4550210/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">Figures 3</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[320,337,1615,1641]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1233,1257]" captionTargetBox="[202,1385,185,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[198,1389,181,1209]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Simplified biogeography of the genus Tegotettix in the islands of Oriental, Wallacean, and Papuan regions. This distribution map shows species of the genus Tegotettix and their accompanying species groups (marked by color, except for the new species which is marked red in the distribution map). Drawn by Josip Skejo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4550214/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="202">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
